v-ff2e5701><button type="button" class="active category-resources__sort-opt" data-v-ff2e5701> Newest </button><button type="button" class="category-resources__sort-opt" data-v-ff2e5701> Oldest </button></div><form class="category-resources__search" data-v-ff2e5701><input id="category-search" value="" type="search" placeholder="Search" autocomplete="off" data-v-ff2e5701><button type="submit" data-v-ff2e5701>Search</button></form></div><div class="category-resources__content" data-v-ff2e5701><div class="category-resources__grid" data-v-ff2e5701><!--[--><div class="blog-card category-resources__item" data-v-ff2e5701 data-v-415a7f80><div class="blog-card__wrapper" data-v-415a7f80><div class="blog-card__image-wrapper" data-v-415a7f80><a href="/all-resources/ocr-reads-the-plate-computer-vision-runs-the-yard" class="" aria-label="Read more about {{ story.content.title }}" data-v-415a7f80><img onerror="this.setAttribute(&#39;data-error&#39;, 1)" width="400" height="400" alt="OCR Reads the Plate, Computer Vision Runs the Yard." data-nuxt-img srcset="/storyblok/f/337048/1510x980/058e2ef5d7/computer-vision-at-gate.png 1x, /storyblok/f/337048/1510x980/058e2ef5d7/computer-vision-at-gate.png 2x" class="blog-card__image" src="/storyblok/f/337048/1510x980/058e2ef5d7/computer-vision-at-gate.png" data-v-415a7f80><button class="blog-card__button button label-4 blog-card__button" style="--hover-bg:rgba(5, 36, 36, 1);--hover-color:rgba(171, 255, 2, 1);--base-color:white;" data-v-415a7f80 data-v-d8fa3fef><span class="link-active" data-v-d8fa3fef><!--[-->Read More<!--]--></span></button></a></div><div class="blog-card__content" data-v-415a7f80><p class="blog-card__category" data-v-415a7f80>blog</p><a href="/all-resources/ocr-reads-the-plate-computer-vision-runs-the-yard" class="" aria-label="Read more about {{ story.content.title }}" data-v-415a7f80><h3 class="blog-card__title" data-v-415a7f80>OCR Reads the Plate, Computer Vision Runs the Yard.</h3></a><p class="blog-card__excerpt" data-v-415a7f80>OCR (the &quot;AI camera&quot; most gate vendors actually sell) just reads characters into a string and hands the work back to your guard, dispatcher, and clerk, which is why a faster clipboard never transforms a yard. Terminal&#39;s computer vision reads, then classifies and understands the whole scene, then acts on it (open the gate, hold the fraudulent carrier, route the reefer), turning recorded data into orchestrated decisions worth 4x ROI in year one.</p><!----></div></div></div><div class="blog-card category-resources__item" data-v-ff2e5701 data-v-415a7f80><div class="blog-card__wrapper" data-v-415a7f80><div class="blog-card__image-wrapper" data-v-415a7f80><a href="/all-resources/the-cv-market-is-having-its-saaspocalypse-moment" class="" aria-label="Read more about {{ story.content.title }}" data-v-415a7f80><img onerror="this.setAttribute(&#39;data-error&#39;, 1)" width="400" height="400" alt="The CV Market is Having its SaaSpocalypse Moment" data-nuxt-img srcset="/storyblok/f/337048/628x318/b8322ea2bb/computer-vision-ubiquity.jpeg 1x, /storyblok/f/337048/628x318/b8322ea2bb/computer-vision-ubiquity.jpeg 2x" class="blog-card__image" src="/storyblok/f/337048/628x318/b8322ea2bb/computer-vision-ubiquity.jpeg" data-v-415a7f80><button class="blog-card__button button label-4 blog-card__button" style="--hover-bg:rgba(5, 36, 36, 1);--hover-color:rgba(171, 255, 2, 1);--base-color:white;" data-v-415a7f80 data-v-d8fa3fef><span class="link-active" data-v-d8fa3fef><!--[-->Read More<!--]--></span></button></a></div><div class="blog-card__content" data-v-415a7f80><p class="blog-card__category" data-v-415a7f80>blog</p><a href="/all-resources/the-cv-market-is-having-its-saaspocalypse-moment" class="" aria-label="Read more about {{ story.content.title }}" data-v-415a7f80><h3 class="blog-card__title" data-v-415a7f80>The CV Market is Having its SaaSpocalypse Moment</h3></a><p class="blog-card__excerpt" data-v-415a7f80>Computer vision is still priced like 2010s enterprise software: six figures up front, long implementations, and a point tool you manage on the side. The economics underneath it have shifted, so Terminal delivers CV at a price built for ROI, folded into the yard platform you already run rather than bolted on beside it.</p><!----></div></div></div><div class="blog-card category-resources__item" data-v-ff2e5701 data-v-415a7f80><div class="blog-card__wrapper" data-v-415a7f80><div class="blog-card__image-wrapper" data-v-415a7f80><a href="/all-resources/beyond-the-yms" class="" aria-label="Read more about {{ story.content.title }}" data-v-415a7f80><img onerror="this.setAttribute(&#39;data-error&#39;, 1)" width="400" height="400" alt="Beyond the YMS: How a Yard Operating System Unlocks Your WMS" data-nuxt-img srcset="/storyblok/f/337048/692x637/dab3d182fc/old-vs-new.jpg 1x, /storyblok/f/337048/692x637/dab3d182fc/old-vs-new.jpg 2x" class="blog-card__image" src="/storyblok/f/337048/692x637/dab3d182fc/old-vs-new.jpg" data-v-415a7f80><button class="blog-card__button button label-4 blog-card__button" style="--hover-bg:rgba(5, 36, 36, 1);--hover-color:rgba(171, 255, 2, 1);--base-color:white;" data-v-415a7f80 data-v-d8fa3fef><span class="link-active" data-v-d8fa3fef><!--[-->Read More<!--]--></span></button></a></div><div class="blog-card__content" data-v-415a7f80><p class="blog-card__category" data-v-415a7f80>blog</p><a href="/all-resources/beyond-the-yms" class="" aria-label="Read more about {{ story.content.title }}" data-v-415a7f80><h3 class="blog-card__title" data-v-415a7f80>Beyond the YMS: How a Yard Operating System Unlocks Your WMS</h3></a><p class="blog-card__excerpt" data-v-415a7f80>The YOS era retires the purpose-built YMS, which is still just a tidier task list, and replaces it with an AI-native system that orchestrates yard missions from data it captures directly. In doing so, it closes the highway-to-warehouse gap and feeds your WMS the clean, live input it needs to finally run at full speed.</p><!----></div></div></div><div class="blog-card category-resources__item" data-v-ff2e5701 data-v-415a7f80><div class="blog-card__wrapper" data-v-415a7f80><div class="blog-card__image-wrapper" data-v-415a7f80><a href="/all-resources/if-trust-in-freight-is-dead-why-is-it-still-running-the-yard-" class="" aria-label="Read more about {{ story.content.title }}" data-v-415a7f80><img onerror="this.setAttribute(&#39;data-error&#39;, 1)" width="400" height="400" alt="If trust in freight is dead, why is it still running the yard?" data-nuxt-img srcset="/storyblok/f/337048/800x533/789821de04/yard-gate.jpg 1x, /storyblok/f/337048/800x533/789821de04/yard-gate.jpg 2x" class="blog-card__image" src="/storyblok/f/337048/800x533/789821de04/yard-gate.jpg" data-v-415a7f80><button class="blog-card__button button label-4 blog-card__button" style="--hover-bg:rgba(5, 36, 36, 1);--hover-color:rgba(171, 255, 2, 1);--base-color:white;" data-v-415a7f80 data-v-d8fa3fef><span class="link-active" data-v-d8fa3fef><!--[-->Read More<!--]--></span></button></a></div><div class="blog-card__content" data-v-415a7f80><p class="blog-card__category" data-v-415a7f80>blog</p><a href="/all-resources/if-trust-in-freight-is-dead-why-is-it-still-running-the-yard-" class="" aria-label="Read more about {{ story.content.title }}" data-v-415a7f80><h3 class="blog-card__title" data-v-415a7f80>If trust in freight is dead, why is it still running the yard?</h3></a><p class="blog-card__excerpt" data-v-415a7f80>Cargo fraud has made the yard the supply chain&#39;s most exposed point, yet yard security and yard management have always been treated as separate problems bought from separate vendors. Terminal&#39;s argument: AI-native development has collapsed that tradeoff, making it possible for the first time to converge both into one system at the gate, where custody actually changes and the decision to lift the arm still matters</p><!----></div></div></div><div class="blog-card category-resources__item" data-v-ff2e5701 data-v-415a7f80><div class="blog-card__wrapper" data-v-415a7f80><div class="blog-card__image-wrapper" data-v-415a7f80><a href="/all-resources/the-4-5-million-freight-theft-that-started-with-a-fake-identity" class="" aria-label="Read more about {{ story.content.title }}" data-v-415a7f80><img onerror="this.setAttribute(&#39;data-error&#39;, 1)" width="400" height="400" alt="The $4.5 Million Freight Theft That Started With a Fake Identity" data-nuxt-img srcset="/storyblok/f/337048/2050x1288/cc16937dab/cargo-theft.png 1x, /storyblok/f/337048/2050x1288/cc16937dab/cargo-theft.png 2x" class="blog-card__image" src="/storyblok/f/337048/2050x1288/cc16937dab/cargo-theft.png" data-v-415a7f80><button class="blog-card__button button label-4 blog-card__button" style="--hover-bg:rgba(5, 36, 36, 1);--hover-color:rgba(171, 255, 2, 1);--base-color:white;" data-v-415a7f80 data-v-d8fa3fef><span class="link-active" data-v-d8fa3fef><!--[-->Read More<!--]--></span></button></a></div><div class="blog-card__content" data-v-415a7f80><p class="blog-card__category" data-v-415a7f80>blog</p><a href="/all-resources/the-4-5-million-freight-theft-that-started-with-a-fake-identity" class="" aria-label="Read more about {{ story.content.title }}" data-v-415a7f80><h3 class="blog-card__title" data-v-415a7f80>The $4.5 Million Freight Theft That Started With a Fake Identity</h3></a><p class="blog-card__excerpt" data-v-415a7f80>For decades, cargo theft looked a certain way. Criminals cut fences, broke locks, and physically stole freight. Security strategies evolved around that reality. Companies invested in gates, cameras, lighting, and guards to keep bad actors out.</p><!----></div></div></div><div class="blog-card category-resources__item" data-v-ff2e5701 data-v-415a7f80><div class="blog-card__wrapper" data-v-415a7f80><div class="blog-card__image-wrapper" data-v-415a7f80><a href="/all-resources/the-driver-is-gone-the-yard-problem-isn-t-" class="" aria-label="Read more about {{ story.content.title }}" data-v-415a7f80><img onerror="this.setAttribute(&#39;data-error&#39;, 1)" width="400" height="400" alt="The Driver Is Gone. The Yard Problem Isn&#39;t." data-nuxt-img srcset="/storyblok/f/337048/1520x872/c718cc5dc1/truck.png 1x, /storyblok/f/337048/1520x872/c718cc5dc1/truck.png 2x" class="blog-card__image" src="/storyblok/f/337048/1520x872/c718cc5dc1/truck.png" data-v-415a7f80><button class="blog-card__button button label-4 blog-card__button" style="--hover-bg:rgba(5, 36, 36, 1);--hover-color:rgba(171, 255, 2, 1);--base-color:white;" data-v-415a7f80 data-v-d8fa3fef><span class="link-active" data-v-d8fa3fef><!--[-->Read More<!--]--></span></button></a></div><div class="blog-card__content" data-v-415a7f80><p class="blog-card__category" data-v-415a7f80>blog</p><a href="/all-resources/the-driver-is-gone-the-yard-problem-isn-t-" class="" aria-label="Read more about {{ story.content.title }}" data-v-415a7f80><h3 class="blog-card__title" data-v-415a7f80>The Driver Is Gone. The Yard Problem Isn&#39;t.</h3></a><p class="blog-card__excerpt" data-v-415a7f80>PepsiCo recently became the first major consumer goods company to deploy fully driverless trucks at scale, operating commercial routes without a human behind the wheel. The trucks are making deliveries to customers such as Walmart and Dollar General, achieving impressive levels of reliability and demonstrating just how quickly autonomous transportation is moving from experiment to reality.</p><!----></div></div></div><div class="blog-card category-resources__item" data-v-ff2e5701 data-v-415a7f80><div class="blog-card__wrapper" data-v-415a7f80><div class="blog-card__image-wrapper" data-v-415a7f80><a href="/all-resources/humanoid-robots-are-entering-logistics-but-the-yard-still-has-to-catch-up-" class="" aria-label="Read more about {{ story.content.title }}" data-v-415a7f80><img onerror="this.setAttribute(&#39;data-error&#39;, 1)" width="400" height="400" alt="Humanoid Robots Are Entering Logistics. But the Yard Still Has to Catch Up." data-nuxt-img srcse